cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for brain lesion detection and segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) domains. The use of denoising autoencoders (DAE) and stacked denoising autoencoders (SDAE) for semi-supervised learning is a key aspect of the paper, which also relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning for segmentation, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
